    @InheritOnly
public interface AbstractThrowingDoubleToFloatFunction1<H extends AbstractThrowingDoubleToFloatFunction1.Handler>
extends AbstractThrowingToFloatFunctionN<H>, net.ashwork.functionality.partial.InputChainableInput<java.lang.Double>, net.ashwork.functionality.partial.UnboxedAll<AbstractThrowingFunction1<java.lang.Double,java.lang.Float,?>,AbstractThrowingToFloatFunction1<java.lang.Double,?>,AbstractThrowingDoubleFunction1<java.lang.Float,?>>
    Represents a function that accepts a double-valued argument and produces a float-valued result or throws a throwable. This is the one-arity specialization of AbstractThrowingToFloatFunctionN. This is the double-consuming primitive specialization of AbstractThrowingToFloatFunction1. This is the float-producing primitive specialization of AbstractThrowingDoubleFunction1. This is the throwing variation of DoubleToFloatFunction1.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    See Also:
    AbstractThrowingDoubleFunction1, AbstractThrowingToFloatFunction1, AbstractThrowingToFloatFunctionN, DoubleToFloatFunction1
    API Note:
    This is an abstract consumer and should not be used directly. It should instead be called by one of its subtypes.
